HEADWORD: Calycle
<hw>Cal"y*cle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L.<ets>calyculus</ets> small flower bud, calyx, dim. of
<ets>calyx</ets>. See <er>Calyx</er>, and cf. <er>Calicle</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A row of small bracts, at the base of the calyx,
on the outside.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

